inputs.question: e para os anos 2023 e 2024

children.output:
Sure, I'll adapt the previous query to include both the years 2023 and 2024.

Here is the SQL query:

```sql
SELECT 
    p.product_id, 
    p.product_name, 
    SUM(st.quantity * p.product_price) AS total_revenue
FROM 
    sales_transaction st
JOIN 
    products p ON st.product_id = p.product_id
WHERE 
    YEAR(st.transaction_date) IN (2023, 2024)
GROUP BY 
    p.product_id, 
    p.product_name
ORDER BY 
    total_revenue DESC
LIMIT 1;
```

This query will find the most profitable product for the years 2023 and 2024.
